[## LECTURE 2.2 — RDS ENCRYPTION AT REST]

40
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:30,000
RDS encryption must be enabled at instance creation.
You cannot enable encryption on an existing unencrypted instance.

41
00:00:30,000 --> 00:01:00,000
If you have a staging database that launched without encryption,
the migration path is clear.
Create an encrypted snapshot. Restore from that snapshot.

42
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:30,000
Update your connection string. Validate. Then delete the original.
Plan a maintenance window for this. It is not immediate.

43
00:01:30,000 --> 00:02:00,000
Let me show you the Terraform configuration for RDS with CMK encryption.

44
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:30,000
In terraform forward slash modules forward slash rds forward slash main dot tf.
Start with an aws_db_parameter_group resource.

45
00:02:30,000 --> 00:03:00,000
Name colon financial-rag dash var dot environment dash pg15.
Family colon postgres15.

46
00:03:00,000 --> 00:03:30,000
First parameter. name colon rds.force_ssl.
value colon one. apply_method colon pending-reboot.
This forces all connections to use TLS.

47
00:03:30,000 --> 00:04:00,000
Second parameter. name colon shared_preload_libraries.
value colon pgaudit comma pg_stat_statements.
This enables database audit logging for Phase 4.

48
00:04:00,000 --> 00:04:30,000
Third parameter. name colon pgaudit.log.
value colon ddl comma role comma read comma write.

49
00:04:30,000 --> 00:05:00,000
Tags include Control colon CC6.6 comma CC6.7.

50
00:05:00,000 --> 00:05:30,000
Now the aws_db_instance resource.
Identifier colon financial-rag dash var dot environment.

51
00:05:30,000 --> 00:06:00,000
Enable encryption at rest.
storage_encrypted set to true.
kms_key_id set to var dot rds_kms_key_arn.

52
00:06:00,000 --> 00:06:30,000
This uses our customer-managed key, not the AWS-managed default.

53
00:06:30,000 --> 00:07:00,000
Storage configuration.
allocated_storage colon one hundred.
max_allocated_storage colon one thousand for autoscaling.
storage_type colon gp3. iops colon three thousand.

54
00:07:00,000 --> 00:07:30,000
Engine configuration.
engine colon postgres. engine_version colon fifteen dot four.
instance_class set from a variable.

55
00:07:30,000 --> 00:08:00,000
Network settings.
db_subnet_group_name and vpc_security_group_ids from variables.
publicly_accessible set to false. Never.

56
00:08:00,000 --> 00:08:30,000
Backup configuration.
backup_retention_period colon thirty for production, seven for staging.
backup_window colon 03:00 dash 04:00 UTC.

57
00:08:30,000 --> 00:09:00,000
maintenance_window colon sun:04:00-sun:05:00.
copy_tags_to_snapshot set to true.
ca_cert_identifier colon rds-ca-rsa2048-g1.

58
00:09:00,000 --> 00:09:30,000
Monitoring configuration.
monitoring_interval colon sixty.
monitoring_role_arn from a variable.
performance_insights_enabled set to true.

59
00:09:30,000 --> 00:10:00,000
performance_insights_retention_period colon seven for free tier.
performance_insights_kms_key_id set to the same CMK.

60
00:10:00,000 --> 00:10:30,000
Safety settings.
deletion_protection set to true for production.
skip_final_snapshot set to false for production.

61
00:10:30,000 --> 00:11:00,000
final_snapshot_identifier uses formatdate.
parameter_group_name set to the parameter group we created.

62
00:11:00,000 --> 00:11:30,000
High availability.
multi_az set to true for production.

63
00:11:30,000 --> 00:12:00,000
The lifecycle block includes prevent_destroy equals true for production.
Never destroy a production database with terraform destroy.

64
00:12:00,000 --> 00:12:30,000
Now if you need to migrate an existing unencrypted staging database,
use the migration script.

65
00:12:30,000 --> 00:13:00,000
Create scripts forward slash migrate-rds-to-encrypted dot sh.
Set INSTANCE_ID to financial-rag-staging.
Set KMS_KEY to the alias ARN.

66
00:13:00,000 --> 00:13:30,000
Step one. Create a snapshot of the current unencrypted instance.
aws rds create-db-snapshot.
Wait for completion.

67
00:13:30,000 --> 00:14:00,000
Step two. Copy the snapshot with encryption.
aws rds copy-db-snapshot. Specify kms-key-id.
Wait for completion.

68
00:14:00,000 --> 00:14:30,000
Step three. Restore the encrypted snapshot as a new instance.
aws rds restore-db-instance-from-db-snapshot.
Set storage-encrypted and kms-key-id.

69
00:14:30,000 --> 00:15:00,000
Step four. Verify encryption on the new instance.
Check StorageEncrypted equals true.

70
00:15:00,000 --> 00:15:30,000
Step five. Update the application connection string in Vault.
Then re-deploy. Validate connectivity.
Then delete the old unencrypted instance.

71
00:15:30,000 --> 00:16:00,000
Collect evidence for the auditor.
Run aws rds describe-db-instances for financial-rag-prod.

72
00:16:00,000 --> 00:16:30,000
Query StorageEncrypted, KmsKeyId, MultiAZ,
BackupRetentionPeriod, and DeletionProtection.

73
00:16:30,000 --> 00:17:00,000
Save the output in JSON format to soc2-evidence under today's date in CC6.6.
Call the file rds-encryption dot json.

74
00:17:00,000 --> 00:17:30,000
Your lab exercise is to apply the RDS Terraform configuration.
If you have an existing unencrypted staging database,
run the migration script.

75
00:17:30,000 --> 00:18:00,000
Verify that storage_encrypted equals true.
Save the describe-db-instances output as evidence.

76
00:18:00,000 --> 00:18:30,000
In the next lecture, we will configure S3 bucket encryption.

