[## LECTURE 2.4 — EBS ENCRYPTION FOR EKS NODES]

107
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:30,000
EBS volumes store data for your Kubernetes workloads.
Persistent volumes for databases, temporary storage for pods,
and the root volumes of your EC2 nodes.

108
00:00:30,000 --> 00:01:00,000
If EBS volumes are not encrypted, an attacker who gains access
to the underlying hypervisor could read your pod data.
This applies even if your application uses encryption at the database level.

109
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:30,000
AWS allows you to set default encryption for all EBS volumes
at the account level. This is the easiest way to ensure coverage.

110
00:01:30,000 --> 00:02:00,000
Enable default EBS encryption for the entire account.
Run aws ec2 enable-ebs-encryption-by-default.

111
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:30,000
Verify it is enabled.
aws ec2 get-ebs-encryption-by-default.
Output should show EbsEncryptionByDefault equals true.

112
00:02:30,000 --> 00:03:00,000
Set the default KMS key to our CMK.
Not the AWS-managed key.
aws ec2 modify-ebs-default-kms-key-id with our key alias.

113
00:03:00,000 --> 00:03:30,000
Verify the default key.
aws ec2 get-ebs-default-kms-key-id.

114
00:03:30,000 --> 00:04:00,000
Now create an encrypted StorageClass for Kubernetes workloads.
In infrastructure forward slash k8s forward slash storage-classes dot yaml.

115
00:04:00,000 --> 00:04:30,000
apiVersion colon storage.k8s.io forward slash v1.
kind colon StorageClass.
metadata colon name colon gp3-encrypted.

116
00:04:30,000 --> 00:05:00,000
Annotations include storageclass dot kubernetes dot io forward slash is-default-class colon true.
description colon Encrypted gp3 storage dash dash default for all workloads dash dash CC6.6.

117
00:05:00,000 --> 00:05:30,000
provisioner colon ebs dot csi dot aws dot com.
parameters colon type colon gp3.
encrypted colon true.

118
00:05:30,000 --> 00:06:00,000
kmsKeyId colon the ARN of our EBS CMK alias.
iops colon three thousand. throughput colon one hundred twenty-five.

119
00:06:00,000 --> 00:06:30,000
reclaimPolicy colon Delete.
volumeBindingMode colon WaitForFirstConsumer.
allowVolumeExpansion colon true.

120
00:06:30,000 --> 00:07:00,000
Apply the StorageClass.
kubectl apply dash f infrastructure forward slash k8s forward slash storage-classes dot yaml.

121
00:07:00,000 --> 00:07:30,000
Verify it is set as default.
kubectl get storageclass.
The default storage class should show gp3-encrypted with parentheses default.

122
00:07:30,000 --> 00:08:00,000
Now any StatefulSet or PVC that does not specify a storage class
will use this encrypted class by default.

123
00:08:00,000 --> 00:08:30,000
Collect evidence for the auditor.
Run aws ec2 get-ebs-encryption-by-default.
Save the output to ebs-default-encryption dot json.

124
00:08:30,000 --> 00:09:00,000
Run kubectl get storageclass gp3-encrypted dash o yaml.
Save the output.

125
00:09:00,000 --> 00:09:30,000
Your lab exercise is to enable default EBS encryption at the account level.
Create the encrypted StorageClass and set it as default.

126
00:09:30,000 --> 00:10:00,000
Verify that new persistent volumes use encryption.
Save the evidence.

127
00:10:00,000 --> 00:10:30,000
In the next lecture, we will configure TLS 1.3 on the ALB.

