[## LECTURE 2.5 — TLS 1.3 ON THE ALB]

128
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:30,000
TLS 1.3 is the current standard for encryption in transit.
It removes all cipher suites with known weaknesses.
RC4, 3DES, SHA-1 are all gone.

129
00:00:30,000 --> 00:01:00,000
TLS 1.3 requires perfect forward secrecy.
Compromising today's traffic does not decrypt past traffic.
And TLS 1.3 handshakes are one round-trip instead of two.

130
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:30,000
AWS provides a security policy called
ELBSecurityPolicy-TLS13-1-0-2021-06.
This enforces TLS 1.3 exclusively. Zero fallback to older versions.

131
00:01:30,000 --> 00:02:00,000
If you need to support older clients, use
ELBSecurityPolicy-TLS13-1-2-2021-06.
That includes TLS 1.2 as a fallback.
Document the business justification in your SOC 2 system description.

132
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:30,000
Let me show you the Ingress configuration for TLS 1.3.

133
00:02:30,000 --> 00:03:00,000
In infrastructure forward slash helm forward slash templates forward slash ingress dot yaml.
apiVersion colon networking.k8s.io forward slash v1.
kind colon Ingress.

134
00:03:00,000 --> 00:03:30,000
metadata colon name colon financial-rag-agent-api.
namespace colon financial-rag.

135
00:03:30,000 --> 00:04:00,000
Annotations include kubernetes.io forward slash ingress.class colon alb.
alb.ingress.kubernetes.io forward slash scheme colon internet-facing.
alb.ingress.kubernetes.io forward slash target-type colon ip.

136
00:04:00,000 --> 00:04:30,000
Critical annotation.
alb.ingress.kubernetes.io forward slash ssl-policy colon
ELBSecurityPolicy-TLS13-1-0-2021-06.
TLS 1.3 only.

137
00:04:30,000 --> 00:05:00,000
alb.ingress.kubernetes.io forward slash ssl-redirect colon four four three.
This forces HTTP to HTTPS redirect.

138
00:05:00,000 --> 00:05:30,000
alb.ingress.kubernetes.io forward slash listen-ports colon
open bracket open brace HTTP colon eighty close brace comma
open brace HTTPS colon four four three close brace close bracket.

139
00:05:30,000 --> 00:06:00,000
alb.ingress.kubernetes.io forward slash certificate-arn colon
template dot Values dot ingress dot certificateArn.

140
00:06:00,000 --> 00:06:30,000
Security headers annotation.
strictTransportSecurity colon max-age equals 31536000 semicolon includeSubDomains semicolon preload.
xContentTypeOptions colon nosniff.
xFrameOptions colon DENY.
contentSecurityPolicy colon default-src quote self quote.

141
00:06:30,000 --> 00:07:00,000
WAF annotation.
alb.ingress.kubernetes.io forward slash wafv2-acl-arn colon template dot Values dot ingress dot wafAclArn.

142
00:07:00,000 --> 00:07:30,000
Logging annotation.
alb.ingress.kubernetes.io forward slash load-balancer-attributes colon
access_logs.s3.enabled equals true comma
access_logs.s3.bucket equals financial-rag-alb-logs-prod comma
idle_timeout.timeout_seconds equals sixty.

143
00:07:30,000 --> 00:08:00,000
Spec section.
rules colon dash host colon api dot financial-rag dot cloudfrugal dot com.
http colon paths colon dash path colon forward slash. pathType colon Prefix.

144
00:08:00,000 --> 00:08:30,000
backend colon service colon name colon financial-rag-agent-api.
port colon number colon eight thousand.

145
00:08:30,000 --> 00:09:00,000
Now verify TLS 1.3 is working.
Run openssl s_client with connect to the API domain on port four four three.
Use the dash tls1_3 flag.

146
00:09:00,000 --> 00:09:30,000
Grep for Protocol and Cipher.
The protocol should be TLSv1.3.
The cipher should be TLS_AES_256_GCM_SHA384 or similar.

147
00:09:30,000 --> 00:10:00,000
Verify return code zero for ok.

148
00:10:00,000 --> 00:10:30,000
Now verify that TLS 1.2 is rejected.
Run openssl s_client with the dash tls1_2 flag.
Grep for alert or handshake failure.

149
00:10:30,000 --> 00:11:00,000
You should see an SSL alert handshake failure.
TLS 1.2 is not supported.

150
00:11:00,000 --> 00:11:30,000
Save the TLS verification as evidence.
