[## LECTURE 2.6 — CERT-MANAGER: AUTOMATED CERTIFICATE RENEWAL]

153
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:30,000
A manually managed certificate will expire. It always does.
Someone goes on holiday. The renewal reminder lands in spam.
Or the person who owns the certificate leaves the company.

154
00:00:30,000 --> 00:01:00,000
Certificate expiry generates an incident, a customer-facing outage,
and an audit finding all at once.
cert-manager with Let's Encrypt solves this.

155
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:30,000
Certificates renew automatically thirty days before expiry.
Prometheus alerts fire if auto-renewal fails.
You never think about certificate expiry again.

156
00:01:30,000 --> 00:02:00,000
Let me show you the cert-manager installation and configuration.

157
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:30,000
Install cert-manager.
kubectl apply dash f the cert-manager release URL.

158
00:02:30,000 --> 00:03:00,000
Wait for all pods to be ready.
kubectl wait dash dash for condition equals ready pod
minus l app.kubernetes.io/name equals cert-manager
minus n cert-manager dash dash timeout equals three hundred seconds.

159
00:03:00,000 --> 00:03:30,000
Verify installation.
kubectl get pods minus n cert-manager.

160
00:03:30,000 --> 00:04:00,000
Now create the ClusterIssuer.
In infrastructure forward slash k8s forward slash cert-manager forward slash cluster-issuer dot yaml.

161
00:04:00,000 --> 00:04:30,000
apiVersion colon cert-manager.io forward slash v1.
kind colon ClusterIssuer.
metadata colon name colon letsencrypt-prod.

162
00:04:30,000 --> 00:05:00,000
spec colon acme colon server colon
https colon forward slash forward slash acme-v02 dot api dot letsencrypt dot org forward slash directory.
email colon security at financial-rag dot com.

163
00:05:00,000 --> 00:05:30,000
privateKeySecretRef colon name colon letsencrypt-prod-key.
solvers colon dash http01 colon ingress colon class colon alb.

164
00:05:30,000 --> 00:06:00,000
Now create the Certificate resource.
apiVersion colon cert-manager.io forward slash v1.
kind colon Certificate.
metadata colon name colon financial-rag-tls. namespace colon financial-rag.

165
00:06:00,000 --> 00:06:30,000
spec colon secretName colon financial-rag-tls.
issuerRef colon name colon letsencrypt-prod. kind colon ClusterIssuer.

166
00:06:30,000 --> 00:07:00,000
commonName colon api dot financial-rag dot cloudfrugal dot com.
dnsNames colon dash api dot financial-rag dot cloudfrugal dot com.

167
00:07:00,000 --> 00:07:30,000
duration colon twenty-one hundred sixty hours. That is ninety days.
renewBefore colon seven hundred twenty hours. That is thirty days before expiry.

168
00:07:30,000 --> 00:08:00,000
privateKey colon algorithm colon RSA. size colon twenty forty-eight.

169
00:08:00,000 --> 00:08:30,000
Apply the ClusterIssuer and Certificate.
kubectl apply dash f the cluster-issuer file.
kubectl apply dash f the certificate file.

170
00:08:30,000 --> 00:09:00,000
Check certificate status.
kubectl get certificate minus n financial-rag.
kubectl describe certificate financial-rag-tls minus n financial-rag.

171
00:09:00,000 --> 00:09:30,000
Now create Prometheus alerts for certificate expiry.
In infrastructure forward slash helm forward slash templates forward slash cert-expiry-alert dot yaml.

17200:09:30,000 --> 00:10:00,000
apiVersion colon monitoring.coreos.com forward slash v1.
kind colon PrometheusRule.
metadata colon name colon cert-expiry-alerts. namespace colon cert-manager.

173
00:10:00,000 --> 00:10:30,000
spec colon groups colon dash name colon certificate-expiry.
rules colon dash alert colon CertificateExpiringSoon.

174
00:10:30,000 --> 00:11:00,000
expr colon certmanager_certificate_expiration_timestamp_seconds minus time divided by 86400 less than thirty.
for colon one hour.

175
00:11:00,000 --> 00:11:30,000
labels colon severity colon warning. control colon CC6.7.
annotations colon summary colon Certificate name expires in value humanizeDuration.

176
00:11:30,000 --> 00:12:00,000
Second alert. CertificateExpired.
expr colon certmanager_certificate_expiration_timestamp_seconds less than time.
for colon zero minutes.

177
00:12:00,000 --> 00:12:30,000
labels colon severity colon critical. control colon CC6.7.
annotations colon summary colon CRITICAL colon Certificate name has EXPIRED.

178
00:12:30,000 --> 00:13:00,000
Third alert. CertificateRenewalFailed.
expr colon certmanager_certificate_ready_status condition equals False equals one.
for colon fifteen minutes.

179
00:13:00,000 --> 00:13:30,000
labels colon severity colon warning. control colon CC6.7.

180
00:13:30,000 --> 00:14:00,000
Collect evidence.
Run aws acm describe-certificate for your ACM certificate ARN.
Query DomainName, NotAfter, Status, and RenewalEligibility.

181
00:14:00,000 --> 00:14:30,000
Save the output to cert-expiry dot json in soc2-evidence under CC6.7.

182
00:14:30,000 --> 00:15:00,000
Your lab exercise is to install cert-manager.
Create the ClusterIssuer and Certificate.
Verify that the certificate is issued.

183
00:15:00,000 --> 00:15:30,000
