[## LECTURE 2.7 — SERVICE-TO-SERVICE ENCRYPTION: CILIUM IPSEC AND DATABASE TLS]

185
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:30,000
TLS on the ALB protects traffic between your users and your load balancer.
But what about traffic between pods inside the cluster?
Or between your API pod and RDS?

186
00:00:30,000 --> 00:01:00,000
Without internal encryption, an attacker who compromises one pod
can sniff plaintext traffic to every other pod.
That is the gap most teams miss.

187
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:30,000
Cilium IPsec mode encrypts all pod-to-pod traffic at the kernel level.
Transparently, without any changes to application code.
Combined with verify-full TLS on database connections,
you achieve end-to-end encryption at every layer.

188
00:01:30,000 --> 00:02:00,000
Let me show you how to enable Cilium IPsec.

189
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:30,000
First, generate a 256-bit pre-shared key for IPsec.
Use dd if equals forward slash dev forward slash urandom to generate thirty-two bytes.
Pipe to xxd dash p dash c sixty-four.

190
00:02:30,000 --> 00:03:00,000
Create a Kubernetes secret with the key.
kubectl create secret generic cilium-ipsec-keys minus n kube-system.
from-literal keys equals three space rfc4106 open parenthesis gcm open parenthesis aes close parenthesis close parenthesis space the key space one hundred twenty-eight.

191
00:03:00,000 --> 00:03:30,000
Now patch the Cilium ConfigMap to enable IPsec.
kubectl patch configmap cilium-config minus n kube-system.
type merge dash p with data.enable-ipsec equals true and data.ipsec-key-file equals forward slash etc forward slash ipsec forward slash keys.

192
00:03:30,000 --> 00:04:00,000
Restart the Cilium DaemonSet to apply the changes.
kubectl rollout restart daemonset slash cilium minus n kube-system.
Wait for rollout to complete.

193
00:04:00,000 --> 00:04:30,000
Verify IPsec is active.
kubectl exec minus n kube-system ds forward slash cilium dash dash cilium encrypt status.
Look for Encryption colon IPsec and Node-to-node encryption colon Enabled.

194
00:04:30,000 --> 00:05:00,000
Now configure application-level TLS for PostgreSQL.

195
00:05:00,000 --> 00:05:30,000
In src forward slash financial_rag forward slash storage forward slash database dot py.
Create a DatabaseClient class.

196
00:05:30,000 --> 00:06:00,000
Set a constant RDS_CA_URL to the AWS RDS certificate bundle.
Set CA_CERT_PATH to forward slash tmp forward slash rds-ca-bundle dot pem.

197
00:06:00,000 --> 00:06:30,000
In the init method, download the CA certificate if not present.
Create an SSL context with ssl dot create_default_context.
Set cafile to the CA certificate path.

198
00:06:30,000 --> 00:07:00,000
Set verify_mode to ssl dot CERT_REQUIRED.
Set check_hostname to True.
This is verify-full mode.

199
00:07:00,000 --> 00:07:30,000
Build the DSN string but do not pass SSL parameters in the DSN.
asyncpg takes SSL as a separate context parameter.

200
00:07:30,000 --> 00:08:00,000
In the connect method, create a pool using asyncpg dot create_pool.
Pass dsn and ssl equals ssl_ctx.

201
00:08:00,000 --> 00:08:30,000
Add a health_check method.
Acquire a connection. Run SELECT ssl FROM pg_stat_ssl.
Assert that ssl_in_use is True.

202
00:08:30,000 --> 00:09:00,000
Now configure Redis TLS.

203
00:09:00,000 --> 00:09:30,000
In src forward slash financial_rag forward slash storage forward slash cache dot py.
Create a CacheClient class.

204
00:09:30,000 --> 00:10:00,000
In the init method, create an SSL context with ssl dot create_default_context.
Set verify_mode to CERT_REQUIRED and check_hostname to True.

205
00:10:00,000 --> 00:10:30,000
Create a Redis client using redis dot asyncio dot Redis.
Pass host, port, password, ssl equals True, ssl_context equals ssl_ctx.

206
00:10:30,000 --> 00:11:00,000
Set decode_responses equals True.
Set socket_timeout equals five and socket_connect_timeout equals five.

207
00:11:00,000 --> 00:11:30,000
Add a health_check method.
Run await self dot _redis dot ping.
Return True if successful.

208
00:11:30,000 --> 00:12:00,000
Now verify database TLS.
Run kubectl exec into the API deployment.
Run psql with the database URL.
Execute SELECT ssl comma version comma cipher FROM pg_stat_ssl.

209
00:12:00,000 --> 00:12:30,000
The output should show t for ssl, TLSv1.3 for version,
and TLS_AES_256_GCM_SHA384 for cipher.

210
00:12:30,000 --> 00:13:00,000
Save this as evidence.
Redirect the output to a file in soc2-evidence under CC6.7.
Call it rds-tls-status dot txt.

211
