[## LECTURE 2.8 — FIELD-LEVEL ENCRYPTION AND THE COMPLETE ENCRYPTION AUDIT]

215
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:30,000
RDS encryption at rest protects data if someone steals the underlying storage.
A physical disk, a snapshot, an unintended backup copy.
But it does not protect against an authorized database administrator.

216
00:00:30,000 --> 00:01:00,000
If the DBA role can read the table, they see plaintext user queries and answers.
For confidentiality, PII fields need field-level encryption.
So that even a database administrator with full SELECT access cannot read them.

217
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:30,000
We will use Fernet from the cryptography library.
Fernet includes an HMAC. Tampered ciphertexts are rejected.
Fernet includes a timestamp for rotation auditing.
Fernet is authenticated encryption. It prevents chosen-ciphertext attacks.

218
00:01:30,000 --> 00:02:00,000
The master key lives in Vault at secret slash financial-rag slash field-encryption-key.
It is injected via Vault Agent sidecar at forward slash vault forward slash secrets forward slash field-encryption-key.
Never in environment variables. Never in config files. Never in Git.

219
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:30,000
Let me show you the field encryption implementation.

220
00:02:30,000 --> 00:03:00,000
In src forward slash financial_rag forward slash storage forward slash encryption dot py.
Create a class FieldEncryption.

221
00:03:00,000 --> 00:03:30,000
Define a class constant _SALT.
This is non-secret but stable. Changing it requires re-encrypting all data.

222
00:03:30,000 --> 00:04:00,000
In the init method, if no master key is provided, load from Vault.
Then derive the key using PBKDF2HMAC with SHA-256.
Iterations set to forty-eight thousand. That is the OWASP 2023 recommendation.

223
00:04:00,000 --> 00:04:30,000
Create a Fernet cipher with the derived key.

224
00:04:30,000 --> 00:05:00,000
Add an encrypt method.
If plaintext is empty, return empty string.
Return cipher.encrypt of plaintext encoded, then decoded.

225
00:05:00,000 --> 00:05:30,000
Add a decrypt method.
If ciphertext is empty, return empty string.
Return cipher.decrypt of ciphertext encoded, then decoded.

226
00:05:30,000 --> 00:06:00,000
Add a static method hash_for_lookup.
Return SHA-256 hash of the value.
This allows queries by hash without decryption.

227
00:06:00,000 --> 00:06:30,000
Add a private static method _derive_key.
PBKDF2HMAC with SHA-256, length thirty-two, the salt, and forty-eight thousand iterations.
Return base64 URL safe encoded result.

228
00:06:30,000 --> 00:07:00,000
Add a private static method _load_from_vault.
Read the key from forward slash vault forward slash secrets forward slash field-encryption-key.
If running locally, fall back to environment variable FIELD_ENCRYPTION_KEY.

229
00:07:00,000 --> 00:07:30,000
Now update the AnalysisRepository to use field encryption.

230
00:07:30,000 --> 00:08:00,000
In src forward slash financial_rag forward slash storage forward slash repositories forward slash analysis dot py.
Add an encryption parameter to the init method.

231
00:08:00,000 --> 00:08:30,000
In record_analysis, encrypt the question before storage.
Encrypt the user email if provided.
Store a hash of the user email for lookup.
Store a hash of the client IP for lookup.

232
00:08:30,000 --> 00:09:00,000
The answer is not PII. It is stored plaintext.

233
00:09:00,000 --> 00:09:30,000
Add a method get_by_user.
Hash the user email. Query by user_email_hash.
No decryption needed for the lookup.

234
00:09:30,000 --> 00:10:00,000
Now let me show you the complete encryption audit script.

235
00:10:00,000 --> 00:10:30,000
Create scripts forward slash encryption-audit dot sh.

236
00:10:30,000 --> 00:11:00,000
The script checks every encryption layer in sequence.
CC6.6 for encryption at rest. CC6.7 for encryption in transit.

237
00:11:00,000 --> 00:11:30,000
First, check KMS key rotation for all aliases.
RDS, S3, EBS. Each must show rotation enabled.

238
00:11:30,000 --> 00:12:00,000
Second, check RDS encryption for production and staging.
Both must show StorageEncrypted equals true.

239
00:12:00,000 --> 00:12:30,000
Third, check S3 bucket encryption for each bucket.
Each must show SSEAlgorithm equals aws:kms.

240
00:12:30,000 --> 00:13:00,000
Fourth, check EBS default encryption.
Must be true.

241
00:13:00,000 --> 00:13:30,000
Fifth, check external TLS version.
Must be TLS 1.3. TLS 1.2 must be rejected.

242
00:13:30,000 --> 00:14:00,000
Sixth, check HTTP to HTTPS redirect.
Return code must be 301 or 302.

243
00:14:00,000 --> 00:14:30,000
Seventh, check certificate validity.
Days remaining must be greater than thirty.

244
00:14:30,000 --> 00:15:00,000
Eighth, check Cilium IPsec.
Must show Encryption equals IPsec.

245
00:15:00,000 --> 00:15:30,000
Ninth, check PostgreSQL TLS.
Must show ssl equals t.

246
00:15:30,000 --> 00:16:00,000
Tenth, check Redis TLS.
Must return PONG successfully.

247
00:16:00,000 --> 00:16:30,000
The script counts passes, fails, and warnings.
If any fail, it exits with code one.

248
00:16:30,000 --> 00:17:00,000
If the dash dash save-evidence flag is passed,
it saves the report to soc2-evidence under today's date.
Call it encryption-audit-dash date dot txt.

249
00:17:00,000 --> 00:17:30,000
Run the audit script.
chmod plus x scripts forward slash encryption-audit dot sh.
dot forward slash scripts forward slash encryption-audit dot sh dash dash save-evidence.

250
00:17:30,000 --> 00:18:00,000
Review the output. Every line should start with a green check mark.
If you see any red X, those are your remediation items.

251
